# 4.1 Size column has sizes in Kb as well as Mb. To analyze, youll need to convert these to numeric.
# Extract the numeric value from the column
# multiply the value by 1,000, if size is mentioned in Mb

def MtoK(b):
    if b[len(b) -1: ] == 'M':
        return(float(b[0: len(b) -1 ])*1000)
    elif b[len(b) -1: ] == 'K' or  b[len(b) -1: ] == 'k':
        return(float(b[0: len(b) -1 ]))
    else:
        return b
In [12]:
df.Size = df.Size.apply(MtoK)

""" 4.3 Installs field is currently stored as string and has values like 1,000,000+. 
Treat 1,000,000+ as 1,000,000
remove +, , from the field, convert it to integer"""

def remove_char(val):
    return(int(val.replace(',','').replace('+','')))
